      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tech 2010</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Andrea Wolper letter scores Andrew Sullivan, in June 11 article in special issue, for giving little thought to how musicians and writers can survive if high-tech theft is allowed to continue; photo</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Invoking Marx as a justification for high-tech theft is pitiful, and Andrew Sullivan doesn't give a thought to how musicians and writers are supposed to survive as long as we don't actually live in a communist society (The Way We Live Now: ''Dot-communist Manifesto''). Or perhaps he is advocating only stealing from musicians who are already rich -- because people bought their albums.</p>
        <p>Andrea Wolper</p>
        <p>New York</p>
      </block>
